  "text": "There are no many data highlighting the relationship between OTs and activation of lymphocytes T-cells in a Th1 and Th2 response in respiratory diseases. In this sense, most of analyses of the behavior of the immune system in this scenario are in allergic diseases, such as asthma studies. In an allergic inflammation, there is substantial evidence showing a relevant infiltration of lymphocyte helper type 2 cells bronchoalveolar lung tissue. This subpopulation of lymphocytes is increased in the lungs of allergic asthmatics, as well as increased levels of IL-4, interleukin 5, and IL-10 cytokines, and interestingly the level of Th2 cytokines appears to correlate with the severity of disease [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
